### Arch Insurance Lab - quote-to-bind smoke test
### Run these top-to-bottom in IntelliJ (click the green arrow by each request).
### IntelliJ captures the returned ids into variables, so later steps reuse them.

### 1. Create a customer  -> 201 Created
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Ada",
  "lastName": "Lovelace",
  "email": "ada.lovelace@example.com",
  "dateOfBirth": "1990-12-10"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("customerId", response.body.id);
    client.test("customer created", () => client.assert(response.status === 201));
%}

### 2. Fetch the customer  -> 200 OK
GET http://localhost:8081/api/v1/customers/{{customerId}}

### 3. Price a quote for that customer  -> 201 Created
POST http://localhost:8082/api/v1/quotes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "{{customerId}}",
  "productType": "AUTO",
  "coverageAmount": 50000
}

> {%
    client.global.set("quoteId", response.body.id);
    client.test("quote is QUOTED", () => client.assert(response.body.status === "QUOTED"));
%}

### 4. Bind the quote into a policy  -> 201 Created
POST http://localhost:8083/api/v1/policies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "{{customerId}}",
  "quoteId": "{{quoteId}}"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("policyId", response.body.id);
    client.test("policy is ACTIVE", () => client.assert(response.body.status === "ACTIVE"));
%}

### 5. Fetch the policy  -> 200 OK
GET http://localhost:8083/api/v1/policies/{{policyId}}

###############################################################################
# Failure cases - these SHOULD return errors (RFC 7807 ProblemDetail bodies)
###############################################################################

### 6. Bind with a customer that does not exist  -> 422 Unprocessable Entity
POST http://localhost:8083/api/v1/policies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "quoteId": "{{quoteId}}"
}

### 7. Bind a quote that belongs to a different customer  -> 422
POST http://localhost:8083/api/v1/policies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "{{customerId}}",
  "quoteId": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111"
}

### 8. Create a customer with a bad payload  -> 400 Bad Request (validation)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "",
  "lastName": "NoEmail",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "dateOfBirth": "2999-01-01"
}
